===Talking to Leela===
* '''Player:''' You must be Leela. Your father sent me to help rescue Prince Ali.
* '''Leela:''' Yes, he sent word ahead that you'd be coming. Are you aware of the plan?
* '''Player:''' I need to obtain a copy of the key to the Prince's cell, create a disguise for him that makes him look like Keli and then break him out of the jail.
* '''Leela:''' I'd say that's a good summary. Now, do you have any questions for me about any part of the plan?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Any ideas for the key?}}
** '''Player:''' Any ideas for the key?
** '''Leela:''' Keli keeps it on her at all times, on a chain around her neck. If you can convince her to show it to you, you might be able to use some soft clay to take an imprint.
** {{tcond|If the player hasn't obtained the [[key print]] yet:}}
*** '''Player:''' That doesn't sound easy.
*** '''Leela:''' My suggestion is that you pretend to be interested in joining her bandits. From there, you should be able to steer the conversation towards the key.
*** '''Leela:''' Once you have the imprint, take it to my father along with a bronze bar. He'll then be able to make us a copy.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** {{tcond|If the player has the key print in their inventory:}}
