*** '''Leela:''' Then you should take it to my father along with a bronze bar. He'll then be able to make us a copy.
*** {{tact|continues}}
** '''Leela:''' Do you have any other questions about the plan?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Any ideas for the disguise?}}
** '''Player:''' Any ideas for the disguise?
** '''Leela:''' To make the Prince look like Keli, you'll need a blonde wig and a pink skirt. You'll also want some skin paste to hide the black eye he got when they captured him.
** '''Leela:''' There's an old sailor in the village who makes rope. Perhaps he could make you a wig. Don't forget to dye it once you have one.
** '''Leela:''' For the skin paste, there's a local witch who's apparently an expert on all sorts of potions. I'm sure she could make you some. I hear she also sells dye, if you need some for the wig.
** '''Leela:''' Finally there's the skirt. I imagine you could just buy one from any clothes shop. Thessalia's Fine Clothes in Varrock is probably the closest.
** '''Leela:''' Do you have any other questions about the plan?
** {{tact|other}}
* {{topt|Don't think so. I'll go and prepare.}}
